{
  "text": "as correcting for selection in panel data. Assuming that selection enters the equation as a fixed individual effect (which may be correlated with the explanatory variables) then using fixed effect estimation provides consistent estimates of the parameters of interest (cf. [CITATION_1] . In the model depicted here, the fixed effects within each cohort are captured by a cohort effect and fixed effects that vary by education group are captured by the education dummy variables.",
  "correct_citation": {
